                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301028-229-off1282 t18301028-229-crimeloc1284"></join> on the 22nd of October; I fell asleep, and when I awoke my hat was gone - the prisoner had been sitting a little distance from me; he returned, and I accused him of it - he denied it; Mr. Spring's young man said he saw a man with a hat on, which he thought was not his- and the next day the prisoner went and showed me where it was - this is the hat; I found it where the prisoner pointed it out.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He said if I would give him his hat he would liberate me, and say nothing about it.</p>
